# Plan: Add a 'thunderball' time_base option to Thunderball/RunPlots.m

## Context

`RunPlots.m` selects how the plot time axis is offset via `opts.time_base`, a
`switch` with two cases (lines 62–73):
- `'avionics'` — no offset: `f_t = @(t_us) t_us*1E-6` (raw avionics seconds).
- `'log_start'` — subtract the first `actuator_outputs_2` timestamp so time starts
  at 0: `f_t = @(t_us) (t_us - to)*1E-6`.

The default is `'avionics'` (line 15). The user wants a new, explicitly-named
`'thunderball'` time-base option that applies the log-start offset, while keeping
`'avionics'` as the default and leaving `'log_start'` intact. The sibling
`/home/choudhury/repos/kwx/Tpro/RunPlots.m` has the same switch (referencing
`actuator_outputs_0` instead of `_2`) and was reviewed for the pattern.

Decisions confirmed with user:
- Add `'thunderball'` as a **new** case (do not rename `'log_start'`; keep it).
- `'thunderball'` behaves the same as `'log_start'` (subtract first
  `actuator_outputs_2` timestamp — log-start relative).
- Default stays `'avionics'` (line 15 unchanged).
- Do **not** modify the wrapper `run_plots.m` (case 100 stays on the avionics
  default; `'thunderball'` is opt-in via `opts.time_base`).

## Change

Single file: `/home/choudhury/repos/kwx/Thunderball/RunPlots.m`

